    <tags>pinelabs mcp payments fastmcp model-context-protocol admin</tags>
    <summary>Official Pine Labs MCP Server exposing Pine Labs payment APIs over the Model Context Protocol (stdio).</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
Pine Labs MCP Server is the official Model Context Protocol (MCP) server for Pine Labs payment APIs.

It lets MCP-compatible clients (Claude Desktop, Cursor, VS Code Copilot, etc.) interact with Pine Labs
Online to create and manage payment links, orders, subscriptions, plans, presentations, UPI intent QR
payments, refunds, and merchant analytics over a stdio transport.

This Chocolatey package is a thin wrapper that:

* Installs Python 3.10+ (via the `python3` Chocolatey dependency).
* Installs the official `pinelabs-mcp-server` distribution from PyPI.
* Registers a `pinelabs-mcp-server` shim on PATH so MCP clients can launch the server.

Usage after install:

    pinelabs-mcp-server stdio --client-id <ID> --client-secret <SECRET> --env uat

Note: this `pinelabs-mcp-server` command is the raw Python stdio server. For a
higher-level CLI with `configure`, `setup &lt;client&gt;`, and `test` subcommands,
install the npm package instead: `npm install -g pinelabs-mcp`.

For full configuration, MCP client setup, and tool reference, see:
https://github.com/plural-pinelabs/pinelabs-online-mcp
]]></description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/plural-pinelabs/pinelabs-online-mcp/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md</releaseNotes>

    <dependencies>
      <dependency id="python3" version="3.10.0" />
    </dependencies>
  </metadata>
